1. Definitions

"Software" means this source code, documentation, templates, tests, and other
materials distributed with this license, excluding Third-Party Materials.

"Personal Use" means use by a natural person solely for that person's private,
non-commercial purposes, outside any employment, contract, trade, profession,
organization, or other institutional activity.

"Organizational Use" means any use by, for, on behalf of, or for the benefit of
a company, partnership, employer, client, public authority, non-profit,
educational institution, research institution, or other organization. It also
includes internal use, evaluation, proof-of-concept work, prototyping,
research, development, testing, deployment, support, and training performed in
an organizational or professional context, whether or not money changes hands.

"Written Permission" means a separate license grant executed by the copyright
holder that expressly identifies the licensee, the Software, the permitted
scope of use, and any applicable term or expiration date.

"Verifiable Authorization Credential" means a machine-readable authorization
record issued by the copyright holder and accompanied by a cryptographic
signature verifiable against the authorization public key published with the
Software. A credential is valid only if its signature, project identifier,
licensee, permitted scope, validity period, and revocation status have been
successfully checked.

"Automated System" means an AI model, LLM, coding assistant, autonomous agent,
build agent, deployment agent, or other software acting on instructions or on
behalf of a person or organization.

