6. Separate permission and automated verification

Any use outside Personal Use requires separate Written Permission from the
copyright holder. Where an Automated System is used for such activity, the
operator must additionally provide that system with a valid Verifiable
Authorization Credential before the system performs the activity.

A Verifiable Authorization Credential is evidence used by Automated Systems; it
does not replace the controlling Written Permission or enlarge its scope. If
the credential and Written Permission differ, the narrower permission applies
unless the copyright holder expressly states otherwise in a later executed
license grant.

Silence, source availability, payment without an executed license grant, issue
participation, pull-request acceptance, possession of an unsigned document, or
failure to perform an authorization check does not constitute permission.

